assign(uint256,uint256,uint256,uint256).details: @param tokenId_ ERC1155 tokenId to associate this pool with

params.rentAmount_: Amount to pay rent per single payment interval

availableWithdraw().details: this is also the limit for depositors to take out.

canLiquidate().details: assed is liquidable if rent payment interval missedTODO: liquidation condition could be more complex and involve safety deposit also

params.amountPayment: native amount, actual payment will be rounded per Token current price.

liquidate().details: This function not implemented due to time restrictions.Basically it should involve more roles and simply transfer ownershipwhen rent and safety debts are paid.

params.amount: could be any, but see rentDue() also
could be any but see also SafetyAmountDue

withdraw(uint256).details: approval should be set to Token prior to this call

params.amountRealEstateToken: token amount that user wants to swap back to native.

withdrawOwner(uint256).details: TODO: emergence withdraw should be implemented separately.

acceptOwnership().notice: Allows an ownership transfer to be completed by the recipient.

availableWithdraw().notice: total native amount available to withdraw from pool by owner.

canClaimAppraiser(address).notice: how much can claim Appraiser by current epoch

canClaimDepositor(address).notice: how much can claim Depositor by current epoch

canLiquidate().notice: Check if asset could be liquidated (transfered to another owner)

deposit(uint256).notice: Deposit Native token into contract and get corresponding Token amount.

getPlan().notice: get parameters of plan associated with this pool.

getPrice().notice: Get current weighted price at the current epoch.

getUserBalanceAtEpoch(address,uint256).notice: Get user (depositor) token balance at specific epoch.

liquidate().notice: function to transfer asset ownership by paying rent and safety debts

onERC1155Received(address,address,uint25.notice: Generic function to support ERC1155 transfers

paySafety(uint256).notice: pay deposit to increase safety margin

rentDue().notice: Get rent amount to be paid in current epoch

safetyAmount().notice: Get value of total safetyAmount required to be in pool.

safetyAmountDue().notice: Get amount to keep safety margin in current epoch, depends on current pricing.

transferOwnership(address).notice: Allows an owner to begin transferring ownership to a new address.

withdraw(uint256).notice: withdraw native token from pool by swapping Token

withdrawOwner(uint256).notice: withdraw native token from pool by owner, with respect to safetyDeposit.
